                "img": "https://arxiv.org/html/2604.02486/2604.02486v1/x12.png",
                "caption": "Figure 7:Chain-of-Thought reasoning allows the VLM to explicitly recover the semantic label for each point and essentially convert the task to a verbal problem. However, when the points lack a concrete semantic label, the transcription process becomes harder, resulting in hallucination as shown by the VLM mislabeling the point B as top of rear window instead of the bottom.",
